title: Admiral Back Window, Stockport Town Hall.
description: Admiral Back window, Stockport Town Hall. Beautiful stained glass window, depicting HMS Terror in Foxes Channel in 1837, a man in helmet in robes holding a portrait of a man, and a scroll of words about Sir George Back, Admiral and navigator.

title: Admiral Back Window, Stockport Town Hall.
description: FORTITUDO. Admiral Back window, Stockport Town Hall. Beautiful stained glass window, depicting the HMS Terror in Foxes Channel in 1837. A man in a helmet & robes holding a portrait of a man. The third image is of a scroll with words relating to Sir George Back 1796 taken prisoner by the French, carried across the Alps on a donkey & more about the Admiral and navigation.
